1 4. Notwithstanding subsection 3, an operator of an emergency medical services
2 operation may operate one or more substation ambulance services operations under a
3 single license if:
4 a. The substation ambulance services operation was licensed before December 31 ,
5 2024, and remains continuously licensed;
6 b. The headquarters ambulance services operation is not a substation ambulance
7 services operation of another emergency medical services operation;
8 b.c. The substation ambulance services operation area borders the headquarters
9 ambulance services operation area or borders another substation of the
10 headquarters ambulance services operation;
11 c.d. The headquarters ambulance services operation and the substation ambulance
12 services operation are dispatched by the same entity; and
13 d.e. The operator of the emergency medical services operation pays a license fee for
14 each of its substation ambulance services operations.
15 5. The provisions of this chapter do not apply to an operator from another state which is
16 headquartered at a location outside of this state and transports patients across state
17 lines, but the operator may not treat patients within this state or pick up patients within
18 this state for transportation to locations within this state, except as provided by rule.
19 6. The department of health and human services shall adopt rules for special licenses
20 and waiver provisions for an operator of an emergency medical services operation
21 intended for industrial sites not available to the general public.
